<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1988] OutOfMemoryError in RegionServer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1988</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;RegionServers tend to die with an OutOfMemoryError under load. I expected this problem to go away with the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1927&quot; title=&quot;Scanners not closed properly in certain circumstances (memory leak)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1927&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1927&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in 0.20.2 RC1, but it&apos;s still happening. Also, when this happens the cluster becomes unresponsive, even once the load on the machines has gone back down. Interestingly there are lots and lots of scanner lease expired messages right before the OOM.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Java 1.6.0_16 64bit on CentOS with 3000M max heap&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
